Body: Description: I am preparing for our annual Windows share review and have found that the AIC doesn't resolve these shares. They are resources that will be in the access review. I have a fairly short time-frame, I need to resolve this by 6/9 to stay on track to launch the review on 6/11. Below are the share paths that are not currently recognized by our installation of StealchAUDIT AIC: \eagle.usaa.comusaaeboascm \eagle.usaa.comusaaClaimstf \eagle.usaa.comHRectrans \eagle.usaa.comusaafsbMDS_Quality \eagle.usaa.comusaaProject_Falcon \eagle.usaa.comusaaTCATADMIN

Steps to Reproduce Updated: Start AIC
Navigate to File shares
Some shares that are expected are not showing

What We've Learned Updated: The customer in this case is indicating that there are file shares missing from his AIC. I suspect this is a scan/bulk import issue or possibly scoping that may be excluding the shares.
Next Steps Updated: Awaiting confirmation that system scan and bulk import are working appropriately.
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Ian Ranstrom, Rich Harbaugh
Next Steps Updated: Meeting scheduled to validate scans and settings.
Next Steps Updated: Awaiting job group to finish running and will follow up to ensure missing share are properly showing in the AIC.

What We've Learned Updated: --------
05/27/2025
--------
The missing shares that the customer was looking for are DFS shares. I discovered that all DFS jobs had been disabled and were not running since October 2024.
I enabled the jobs and ran job 1 to enumerate the shares. The missing shares were found and I started the full job group.


The customer in this case is indicating that there are file shares missing from his AIC. I suspect this is a scan/bulk import issue or possibly scoping that may be excluding the shares.
